<BorderPane xmlns="http://javafx.com/javafx/22" xmlns:fx="http://javafx.com/fxml/1" fx:controller="edu.augustana.UI.InstructionsController">
   <center>
      <AnchorPane prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="600.0">
         <children>
            <TabPane prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="600.0" tabClosingPolicy="UNAVAILABLE">
              <tabs>
                <Tab text="Radio">
                  <content>
                    <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" prefHeight="372.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="174.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Before you do anything, you must turn on the radio. This can be done by button in bottom right hand corner of the radio. The button to the left of that is the mute button, which will silence all incoming and outgoing sound. After that, in order to hear anything, you will need to turn the volume up and open both filters. The first filter is a low-pass filter, which filters out noise from outside interference, like the weather.  This is controlled by the knob labeled &quot;FILTER&quot;. If the filter is closed all the way, you won't be able to hear anything. The top slider on the bottom of the radio is a frequency filter. This will filter out incoming CW transmissions if they are far away enough from where you are tuned into, and this filter will also need to be opened in order to hear anything. The bottom slider is your &quot;dial&quot;, which allows you to change the frequency that you are tuned into." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                       <padding>
                                          <Insets top="10.0" />
                                       </padding>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="78.0" prefWidth="576.0" text="You will notice the other knob controls on the radio, the band and tone controls! The band knob controls what meter band you are using, and the default is 10m. The tone knob controls your side tone, or what frequency you output CW at. For all knob controls, it is best to operate them with the scroll wheel. If you don't have a mouse, trying scrolling like you would on any web page." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="94.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Now, how do you actually output some CW? We have two options for you, paddles and a straight key. For the paddles the &quot;J&quot; key will output your dots for as long as you hold the key down. The &quot;K&quot; key will do the same but for your dashes. The &quot;L&quot; key is your straight key, and it will determine dots and dashes based on how long you hold down the button. The straight key needs to be calibrated, so please type in a letter or two so that it knows how quickly or slowly you type." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="49.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Along the top of the screen, there are buttons which control the right panel. You can switch between training and sandbox, and even pull this window back up with the &quot;Instructions&quot; button!" textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                  </content>
                </Tab>
                  <Tab text="Sandbox">
                    <content>
                      <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" layoutX="-1.0" layoutY="-3.0" prefHeight="376.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="51.0" prefWidth="570.0" text="To get to the Sandbox, hit the &quot;Sandbox&quot; button on the title bar. This will give you access to Scenarios and Servers." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                       <padding>
                                          <Insets top="10.0" />
                                       </padding>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="60.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Scenarios are a mode where a specified number of bots will appear, with specified conditions, and the user will have to navigate the scenario depending on what is asked of them. You can create new ones, customize them, and save them to your computer. You can then, later, load that same scenario back up and play through it." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="88.0" prefWidth="575.0" text="There are two types of scenarios: Responsive and AI. When creating a scenario you input all of the desired scenario descriptions, and then you decide whether the scenario will be responsive or AI. A scenario also needs bots! So once you have decided what type your scenario will be, then you can add your bots. You can completely customize your bots by filling in the text boxes in the bot creation window. " textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="93.0" prefWidth="575.0" text="If you create a responsive scenario, then you will have to go through two stages of development for each bot. At the beginning of the scenario, each bot will be saying CQ and then its call sign. Your job is to tell the bot &quot;RO&quot;, then its call sign back to them to tell them roger and that you hear them. After that, then they will play their message where they will tell you what frequency to send a message. Once that is done, then that bot is complete! Then you move onto the next bot in the scenario." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="59.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="For an AI scenario, the bots will be playing CQ and their call sign at random times to try to get you to talk to them. Once you start talking to them, then they will respond to the message you send them or say something random based on the prompt you gave them." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="41.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Servers allow you to connect with other users and talk to them directly. You can create your own server or join others. You can choose whether or not you want to transmit in CW or English." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                    </content>
                  </Tab>
                  <Tab text="Listening Sim">
                    <content>
                      <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" layoutY="-1.0" prefHeight="372.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="99.0" prefWidth="559.0" text="Listening Sim will generate a number of bots based on what the user selected, and these bots will continuously transmit their callsign, wait a few seconds, and then transmit their message. You will be required to translate both their callsign and message and put them in their respective boxes. If you are correct, the message will show up green in the text box. If not, red." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                       <padding>
                                          <Insets top="10.0" />
                                       </padding>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                    </content>
                  </Tab>
                <Tab text="Flashcards">
                  <content>
                    <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" prefHeight="370.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="43.0" prefWidth="579.0" text="The &quot;Flashcards&quot; tab will allow you to practice your CW typing and translating skills in a low stress environment. There are two different training types to choose from, &quot;Listening&quot; and &quot;Typing&quot;." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="58.0" prefWidth="580.0" text="For both of these, you are able to choose between three different sets of possibilities: letters, numbers, and common CW abbreviations/phrases used by HAM radio operators. You can mix and match to your hearts content, so if you only want letters and abbreviations, you can!" textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="48.0" prefWidth="578.0" text="&quot;Listening&quot; training will play a something out in morse code and you will be required to translate what was said back into English, and type it in the Guess box." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="18.0" prefWidth="576.0" text="&quot;Typing&quot; training will ask you to type back the given character in morse code." textFill="WHITE">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="33.0" prefWidth="574.0" text="Whenever you are tired of your training, hit the end training button, and your done!" textFill="WHITE">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children></AnchorPane>
                  </content>
                </Tab>
                  <Tab text="Known Bugs/Issues">
                    <content>
                      <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefHeight="180.0" prefWidth="200.0">
                           <children>
                              <VBox alignment="TOP_CENTER" prefHeight="376.0" prefWidth="600.0" style="-fx-background-color: #606160;">
                                 <children>
                                    <Label prefHeight="41.0" prefWidth="566.0" text="If you hold the straight key down for a long time as your first straight key input, it messes with how we calculate your words per minute, and makes the straight key unusable." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="41.0" prefWidth="566.0" text="When editing a scenario and you change the name, the name would not change on the view of the drop down menu but it will show up if you open the dropdown menu" textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                    <Label prefHeight="57.0" prefWidth="566.0" text="When creating a scenario, you cannot create a bot of a certain type, and then change the type of the scenario to create a different bot. This will cause the scenario to crash. The entire scenario has to be of one type." textFill="WHITE" wrapText="true">
                                       <font>
                                          <Font name="Sitka Heading" size="12.0" />
                                       </font>
                                    </Label>
                                 </children>
                              </VBox>
                           </children>
                        </AnchorPane>
                    </content>
                  </Tab>
              </tabs>
            </TabPane>
         </children>
      </AnchorPane>
   </center>
   <bottom>
      <AnchorPane prefHeight="38.0" prefWidth="600.0" BorderPane.alignment="TOP_CENTER">
         <children>
            <Button fx:id="okButton" alignment="CENTER" layoutX="282.0" layoutY="6.0" mnemonicParsing="false" text="Ok!" />
         </children>
      </AnchorPane>
   </bottom>
</BorderPane>
